DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board held an emergency meeting to address the COVID-19 pan
 demic and approved Resolution 22\, designating identified District public 
 works projects as Essential Governmental Functions to continue operations 
 under the San Mateo Public Health Order.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: ht
 tps://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:board-meeting-2020-04-01-board-meeting-2@rcsd.info
DTSTAMP:20260522T200000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20200401T220000
SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Board Meeting)
DESCRIPTION:The Board approved multiple Bond Program projects across distri
 ct schools\, including modernization work at Adelante Selby School\, archi
 tectural support at Clifford School\, and construction agreements at Taft 
 School. The Board also adopted Resolution 21\, a resolution of emergency r
 elating to COVID-19\, and discussed the district's response to the pandemi
 c.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
URL:https://rcsd.info/meetings/2020-04-01/
LOCATION:District Office, 750 Bradford St, Redwood City, CA 94063
END:VEVENT
