SUMMARY:RCSD Board Meeting (Regular)
DESCRIPTION:Board adopted the Facilities Master Plan (5-0) and approved two
  landmark bond projects: $1.88M Siemens building management system for HVA
 C controls at four schools and the $19.74M Blach Construction GMP for HVAC
  Phase 1 at Adelante Selby\, Hoover\, Roosevelt\, and Taft. Ratified all t
 hree union contracts ($3.24M combined: RCTA $1.54M\, CSEA $986K\, RCAA $71
 7K). Adopted Resolution 25 (year-end budget transfers). Public comment: CS
 EA President Stockton praised scholarship program but expressed concerns a
 bout not feeling respected by the district. First readings on mobile commu
 nication devices drew public comment from parents Mercedes Kwiatkowski and
  Wyatt Hamon supporting phone-free policies. VP Weekly reported using AI t
 o identify Board Policy improvements.\n\nFull agenda and recordings: https
 ://rcsd.info/meetings/2025-06-11/
